Read file content from an uploaded file, local path, or URL

Provides file content based on the input source. You can upload a file, specify a local file path, or provide a URL to a remote file.

Authorizations:
bearerbearer
Request Body schema: multipart/form-data
required
file
string <binary>

Upload a file (optional if filePath or url is provided)

filePath
string

Absolute or relative path to a file on the local file system

url
string

URL of a remote file to fetch content from

generateBlobUrl
boolean

If true, returns content as a base64 blob-style data URL.

Responses

/api/file/read

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json
{
  • "filePath": "/path/to/your/file.ts",
  • "filename": "example.ts",
  • "mimeType": "text/typescript",
  • "language": "typescript",
  • "content": "console.log(\"Hello World\");",
  • "blob": "data:text/plain;base64,SGVsbG8sIFdvcmxkIQ=="
}

Scans specified directories and files for relevant code files

Recursively scans paths, reads content of relevant files, and returns their absolute path, relative path, and content. Uses internal exclusion lists for common development artifacts like node_modules.

Authorizations:
bearerbearer
Request Body schema: application/json
required
scanPaths
required
Array of strings

An array of paths (relative or absolute) to scan. Each path can be a directory or a file. Defaults to ["."].

projectRoot
string

The root directory of the project, used for calculating relative paths. Defaults to process.cwd() if not provided.

verbose
boolean

If true, logs detailed information during scanning.

Responses

/api/file/scan

Request samples

  • Payload
Content type
application/json
{
  • "scanPaths": [
    • ".",
    • "src/auth",
    • "package.json"
    ],
  • "projectRoot": "/media/eddie/Data/projects/nestJS/nest-modules/full-stack",
  • "verbose": false
}

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json
[
  • {
    • "filePath": "/app/src/main.ts",
    • "relativePath": "src/main.ts",
    • "content": "console.log(\"Hello, world!\");"
    }
]

Generate a new resume based on a detailed prompt using Google Gemini

Authorizations:
bearer
Request Body schema: application/json
required
prompt
required
string non-empty

The detailed prompt describing the resume to be generated. This should include personal details, desired job role, experience level, key skills, and any specific sections or formatting requirements.

systemInstruction
string

Optional: Custom system instruction to guide the AI model on how to generate the resume (e.g., "Use a modern, minimalist design", "Focus on leadership experience"). Overrides default instructions.

conversationId
string

Optional: An existing conversation ID to maintain context with the AI model for continued interaction (e.g., if refining a previously generated resume).

Responses

  • "systemInstruction": "Generate the resume strictly in JSON format, outlining each section as a separate object.",
  • "conversationId": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-1234-567890abcdef"
}

LLM Operations

Generate code and file changes using the LLM

Authorizations:
bearer
query Parameters
projectRoot
required
string

Absolute path to the project root directory. Files will be scanned and proposed changes will be relative to this root.

Request Body schema: application/json
required
userPrompt
required
string

The main request or prompt from the user to the AI.

projectRoot
required
string

The absolute path to the root directory of the project being edited.

projectStructure
string

A high-level overview of the project directory structure, typically generated as a tree string or simplified list.

relevantFiles
Array of arrays

An array of relevant files from the project, including their paths and content, for the LLM to analyze or modify.

additionalInstructions
required
string

Additional instructions or constraints for the LLM regarding its behavior, style, or specific requirements.

expectedOutputFormat
required
string

Detailed instructions on the exact JSON format the LLM is expected to return for its response.

scanPaths
required
Array of arrays

An array of paths (relative to projectRoot) to explicitly scan. If not provided, the AI may decide which files to include based on context.

Responses

/api/llm/generate-llm

  • Payload
Content type
application/json

  • "userPrompt": "Implement a new user authentication module with JWT. Include login and register endpoints.",
  • "projectRoot": "/path/to/your/project",
  • "projectStructure": "\nproject-root/\n├── src/\n│ ├── app.module.ts\n│ ├── app.controller.ts\n│ └── main.ts\n├── package.json\n└── tsconfig.json\n",
  • "relevantFiles": [
    • {
      • "filePath": "/path/to/your/project/src/app.module.ts",
      • "relativePath": "src/app.module.ts",
      • "content": "import { Module } from '@nestjs/common';\nimport { AppController } from './app.controller';\nimport { AppService } from './app.service';\n\n@Module({\n imports: [],\n controllers: [AppController],\n providers: [AppService],\n})\nexport class AppModule {}\n"
      },
    • {
      • "filePath": "/path/to/your/project/src/app.controller.ts",
      • "relativePath": "src/app.controller.ts",
      • "content": "import { Controller, Get } from '@nestjs/common';\nimport { AppService } from './app.service';\n\n@Controller()\nexport class AppController {\n constructor(private readonly appService: AppService) {}\n\n @Get()\n getHello(): string {\n return this.appService.getHello();\n }\n}\n"
      }
    ],
  • "additionalInstructions": "Ensure all new code adheres to TypeScript strict mode. Use functional components for React. Avoid external libraries unless specified.",
  • "expectedOutputFormat": "\n{\n \"summary\": \"A brief summary of the proposed changes.\",\n \"thoughtProcess\": \"Detailed explanation of the AI's reasoning and steps taken.\",\n \"changes\": [\n {\n \"filePath\": \"path/to/file.ts\",\n \"action\": \"add\" | \"modify\" | \"delete\",\n \"newContent\": \"Optional: New content for 'add'/'modify'\",\n \"reason\": \"Optional: Explanation for this specific change\"\n }\n ]\n}\n",
  • "scanPaths": [
    • "src/components",
    • "package.json",
    • "README.md"
    ]
}
